# Asset Management Guidelines

## File Naming Conventions
- Icons: Use kebab-case with descriptive names (e.g., `icon-painting-16.png`)
- JSON files: Use descriptive names with version indicators
- PowerShell scripts: Use descriptive names with clear purpose

## Metadata Structure
- Maintain consistent JSON schema for icon data
- Include position, category, tags, and CSS class information
- Track creation and modification dates
- Provide sprite sheet specifications (dimensions, spacing, padding)

## Sprite Sheet Generation
- Support multiple resolutions (16x16, 32x32, 48x48, 64x64)
- Generate multiple format outputs (CSV, JSON, XML)
- Maintain grid-based positioning system
- Include visual grid representation for debugging

## PowerShell Scripts
- Use parameter validation with Mandatory flags
- Implement error handling and progress reporting
- Support batch operations for multiple files
- Provide clear console output for user feedback